description:
This course attempts a concentrated survey of the early years -- primarily the 1790's --of the English Romantic period. Specific texts vary with instructor, but usually include works from Blake, Coleridge, and Wordsworth. 

See the English Department's website at www.english.upenn.edu for a complete description of the current offerings.
name: BRITISH ROMANTICISM: BRITISH LIT., 1770-1800
